<br>
Use the SoTF to pull sarnaks, cockatrices and succulents, round them up, cast Bonds of Force.  I recommend you download and setup one of the timer with it set to 2 mins, the length of BoF.  That way you can judge when your snare will break.  I found that if I just kept running ahead and casting my aoe that snare broke each time just as the mobs started to turn to run.  Quick inferno shock or smaller nuke and it finished them off.  Sarnaks are especially good cause you can just keep aoe'ing until they all die rather than wasting all your mana with small nukes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=troajennmann@graffeswizardcompilation>TroajennMann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/03 7:50:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25585.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> quadin</span><hr size=1> ok pulled an all nighter, well 6 hours worth, of quading the dwarves.  i jus found it easier to kill 2 at time instead of 4.  Maybe this is a good idea till about 44ish, cause then my BoF will last longer than it does now, because when i pull 4 now its like a big pain in the ballz the BoF seems to break randomly on any given mob, if i do the quest for the Staff of T. Flux will this make my chances for quading 4 at a time any better? or is that jus something to gain the aggro minus the castin.  the reason im not quading in OT is simply because the zone jus got boring, i was there for about 10 lvls and jus got sik of it, that and the XP alone from jus soloin 1 camp with 4 dwarves is so much betta than fightin mobs in OT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span c